---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Breadcrumbs from '../components/Breadcrumbs.astro';
---

<BaseLayout 
  title="Privacy Policy - BrewOS"
  description="BrewOS Privacy Policy - Learn how we collect, use, and protect your data when using BrewOS firmware, cloud services, and web applications."
  currentPath="/privacy"
  noindex={true}
>
  <section class="legal-page">
    <div class="container">
      <Breadcrumbs items={[
        { name: "Home", url: "/" },
        { name: "Privacy Policy", url: "/privacy" }
      ]} />
      <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
      <p class="last-updated">Last updated: January 2025</p>

      <div class="content">
        <h2>Introduction</h2>
        <p>
          BrewOS ("we", "our", or "us") is committed to protecting your privacy. 
          This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, and safeguard your information 
          when you use our firmware, web application, and cloud services.
        </p>

        <h2>Information We Collect</h2>
        <h3>Device Data</h3>
        <p>When using BrewOS firmware, we may collect:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Machine temperatures and operational parameters</li>
          <li>Usage statistics (shot counts, brewing times)</li>
          <li>Device identifiers and firmware versions</li>
          <li>Error logs and diagnostic information</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Account Data</h3>
        <p>When you create a BrewOS Cloud account, we collect:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Email address</li>
          <li>Display name</li>
          <li>Authentication credentials (securely hashed)</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Analytics</h3>
        <p>Our website uses Google Analytics to understand how visitors use our site. This may include:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Pages visited and time spent</li>
          <li>Browser and device information</li>
          <li>Approximate geographic location</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>How We Use Your Information</h2>
        <p>We use collected information to:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Provide and improve our services</li>
          <li>Send important updates about your device</li>
          <li>Diagnose and fix technical issues</li>
          <li>Develop new features based on usage patterns</li>
          <li>Ensure security of our systems</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Data Storage and Security</h2>
        <p>
          Your data is stored on secure servers with industry-standard encryption. 
          We implement appropriate technical and organizational measures to protect 
          your personal information against unauthorized access, alteration, or destruction.
        </p>

        <h2>Data Sharing</h2>
        <p>
          We do not sell your personal information. We may share data with:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>Service providers who assist in operating our services</li>
          <li>Law enforcement when required by law</li>
          <li>Other parties with your explicit consent</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Your Rights</h2>
        <p>You have the right to:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Access your personal data</li>
          <li>Request correction of inaccurate data</li>
          <li>Request deletion of your data</li>
          <li>Export your data in a portable format</li>
          <li>Opt out of marketing communications</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Local-Only Mode</h2>
        <p>
          BrewOS can operate entirely locally without any cloud connection. 
          In this mode, no data is transmitted to our servers. All data remains 
          on your local network and device.
        </p>

        <h2>Contact Us</h2>
        <p>
          If you have questions about this Privacy Policy, please contact us at:
          <a href="mailto:privacy@brewos.io">privacy@brewos.io</a>
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .legal-page {
    padding: 140px 0 80px;
    background: var(--cream-100);
  }

  .legal-page h1 {
    font-size: 2.5rem;
    font-weight: 800;
    color: var(--coffee-800);
    margin-bottom: 8px;
  }

  .last-updated {
    color: var(--text-muted);
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    margin-bottom: 48px;
  }

  .content {
    max-width: 800px;
  }

  .content h2 {
    font-size: 1.5rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--coffee-800);
    margin: 40px 0 16px;
  }

  .content h3 {
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--coffee-700);
    margin: 24px 0 12px;
  }

  .content p {
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    line-height: 1.8;
    margin-bottom: 16px;
  }

  .content ul {
    margin: 16px 0;
    padding-left: 24px;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
  }

  .content li {
    margin-bottom: 8px;
    line-height: 1.7;
  }

  .content a {
    color: var(--accent);
    text-decoration: none;
  }

  .content a:hover {
    text-decoration: underline;
  }
</style>

